title: Trump ruthlessly mocks 'radical left' pro-Maduro protesters
description: US President Donald Trump has mocked “radical left” pro-Venezuela protestors during a wide-ranging address.  Trump’s comments come following Operation Absolute Resolve, which saw US forces descend on the city of Caracas and capture former Venezuelan leader Nicholas Maduro.  The Venezuelan is currently detained in New York and has been indicted on a range of charges, including Narco-Terrorism Conspiracy and Cocaine Importation Conspiracy.  Prior to Trump ridiculing the “radical left”, he touted the raid as an “amazing military feat” The president said the operation was “complex,” involving 152 aircraft.

title: Inflation rises 3.4 per cent in the year to November
description: The latest inflation data has just been released by the Bureau of Statistics ahead of the first interest rate decision of 2026.  The data reveals an inflation rise of 3.4 per cent in the year to November.  This is better than what the market was expecting, as they were expecting 3.6 per cent.   This is a slightly delayed batch of information, as it doesn’t take into account the Boxing Day sales period and post Black Friday sales.  It is an encouraging figure, but it is not a firm indicator that a rate rise is necessarily coming, although it shows inflation is heading in the right direction.

title: 'If you practice radical Islamic hatred, you should be deported': Sussan Ley
description: Opposition Leader Sussan Ley discusses radical Islamic extremism within Australia.   “If you have listened to the prime minister and his ministers over the last few weeks, they actually haven’t confronted the issue of radical Islamic extremism,” Ms Ley said.  “If you practice radical Islamic hatred, if you incite violence, if you glorify terrorism, and you are not an Australian citizen, you will be deported, and if you are an Australian citizen, you will be arrested.”

title: Venezuela’s future remains uncertain following Maduro’s capture
description: US lawmakers have expressed concern over Venezuela’s future in the aftermath of President Donald Trump’s military operation.  Questions are being raised over what the next steps are and whether other countries are on the line.  This comes as there’s a renewed push for Congress to have more say in how and when the US uses military force.

title: Donald Trump hilariously reveals Melania hates it when he dances in public
description: US President Donald Trump has hilariously revealed that First Lady Melania Trump hates it when he dances, calling it “not presidential”.  Trump defended his dancing, saying crowds “go crazy” when he dances.  During the address, Trump also accused the captured former leader of Venezuela, Nicolas Maduro, of trying to imitate his dance.  The Venezuelan is currently detained in New York and has been indicted on a range of charges, including Narco-Terrorism Conspiracy and Cocaine Importation Conspiracy.

title: ‘Got everyone’s attention’: Trump’s threat to Greenland loomed over Paris meeting
description: CNN Senior International Correspondent Melissa Bell explains how US President Donald Trump’s threat to Greenland loomed over the Coalition of the Willing Summit in Paris.  “What we’ve seen over the last few days … has certainly got everyone’s attention here in Europe,” Ms Bell said.  “The spectre of Greenland that was floating all around and over it.”

title: ‘It’s crazy’: Trump mocks transgender athletes
description: US President Donald Trump has mocked transgender athletes while addressing Republican lawmakers.   He singled out weightlifting as a particular concern.  “It’s crazy,” Mr Trump said.

title: ‘Not great news for interest rates’: Inflation rises 3.4 per cent in year to November
description: EQ Economics Managing Director Warren Hogan says inflation rising 3.4 per cent in the year to November is still “not great news overall for interest rates”.

title: Crowd in hysterics as Trump hilariously impersonates trans weightlifter
description: Donald Trump had a crowd of Republicans in hysterics yesterday when he hilariously impersonated a trans weightlifter competing.

title: ‘We inherited a mess’: Trump blasts Biden administration’s economic failures
description: US President Donald Trump blames the Biden administration for the failures of the American economy.  “We inherited high prices, we inherited a mess, we inherited the greatest inflation in history,” Mr Trump said.  “We now have the hottest economy in the history of our country.”

title: Donald Trump ruthlessly blasts Nancy Pelosi over major ‘scandal’
description: US President Donald Trump has called out former House speaker Nancy Pelosi on the January 6 anniversary for denying 10,000 soldiers.

title: ‘Fat drug’: Ozempic cost slashed after Trump deal
description: US President Donald Trump boasts of his drug-pricing deals with pharmaceutical manufacturers to bring prices in line with those paid in other developed nations.  “I said, France, your healthcare for prescription drugs is going to go up triple,” Mr Trump said.  “Just as an example, Ozempic is $80 in London, and it $1300 in New York, the fat drug.”

title: Tasmania's premier backs calls for royal commission into Bondi attack
description: Tasmania Premier Jeremy Rockliff has become the second state or territory leader to back a federal royal commission into the Bondi terror attack and antisemitism.  Following Queensland Premier David Crisafulli, Mr Rockcliff adds his name to a growing list of people calling on Prime Minister Anthony Albanese to establish the enquiry.  Tasmania has the smallest Jewish population of any state or territory, at just under 400 people.

title: Donald Trump’s popularity ‘ticks up a notch’ following Venezuelan Maduro operation
description: US Studies Centre’s Lester Munson claims US President Donald Trump’s popularity may have “ticked up a notch” following the military’s operation in Venezuela and the capture of the country’s leader, Nicolas Maduro.  “It appears that his popularity with the American people may have ticked up a notch,” he told Sky News Australia.  “I think most Americans feel there’s no doubt that Nicolas Maduro was a huge problem for the US.”

title: Anthony Albanese attends final funeral for Bondi terror attack victim
description: Prime Minister Anthony Albanese has attended the final Bondi victim’s funeral, Peter Meagher, at Saint Mary’s Cathedral.   This is an important moment, given it marks the first time Prime Minister Albanese has publicly attended one of the funerals of the Bondi victims.  He reportedly didn’t attend other funerals out of respect, because their families didn’t view that the Prime Minister would be welcomed.   He was joined by New South Wales Premier Chris Minns, New South Wales Police Commissioner Mal Lanyon, and Opposition Leader Sussan Ley.   Peter was attending the Chanukah by the Sea event as a freelance photographer before he was fatally shot.
